tr.td: <string name="battery_status_time_to_full_unknown">Time To Full: Calculating - check back later</string>
<string name="preferences_show_notification_sum">See the notification without the notification icon</string>

<string name="preferences_theme_getmore_msg">This will search for more Battery Monitor themes. GSam Labs does not control or approve all themes, so if the theme does't work, contact the the developer of the theme.

Download and install the theme, then come back to this menu to see the available themes.

Did you know you can create your own themes? See http://badassbatterymonitor.blogspot.com for details on how!</string>
<string name="preferences_widget_back_msg">Make the widget background completely transparent, allowing your wallpaper to show through.</string>
<string name="preferences_overlay_icon_sum">Overlay the stock battery icon. Location, size, etc. are all fully configurable.</string>
<string name="preferences_overlay_icon_configure_sum">Configure the overlay icon\'s size, location, background color, brightness, and more.</string>
<string name="preferences_overlay_icon_configure_invalid">Unable to launch configuration. Open the icon pack manually to configure.</string>

<string name="preferences_overlay_icon_notvalid_msg">Select a different theme, and try again.\n\nOverlay Icons are only supported by external Icon Packs. Select Get More Themes from the Battery Icon Theme menu to find an external icon pack. All Icon Packs provided by GSam Labs support overlay icons. Third party icon packs may not support overlays.</string>
<string name="preferences_app_theme_sum">Use a dark theme for the app screens</string>
<string name="preferences_time_left_sum">Calculate time left based on the usage over this time scale.</string>
<string name="preferences_profiles_screen_summary">Advanced - Edit the power usage profiles used to calculate all values</string>
<string name="preferences_power_per_percent_summary">Amount of power used for each percent drop in battery. Zero out if you change profile settings.</string>

<string name="preferences_power_per_percent_dlgtext">Comma separated in the form POWER_USED_PER_PERCENT_DROP,TOTAL_PERCENT_MEASURED. This value is constantly updated - the longer you run, the more accurate it gets. Whenever you change a Power Profile setting however, you should clear this field, and let the app regenerate.</string>

<string name="preferences_time_per_percent_summary">Reset the calculated value for average amount of time your device lasts for a full battery cycle. Currently %1$s (%2$sm / percent calculated over %3$01d percentages)</string>
<string name="preferences_stats_since_summary">View statistics since last unplugged, or since last full charge</string>
<string name="preferences_power_profiles_edit_summary">Customize your power profile. The custom values will only be used if the custom profile is enabled.</string>
<string name="profedit_title">Modify the values below to change how your time remaining and App Sucker times are calculated</string>
<string name="profedit_custom_values_saves">Saved custom values. You may re-enable manufacturing defaults in the preferences screen.</string>
<string name="preferences_clear_chart_history_sum">Click here to clear the local cached file for chart history.</string>

<string name="preferences_clear_history_stats_sum">Click here to reset the battery statistics. This will remove all statistic history. It\'s equivalent to doing a full charge and unplug. All statistics are reset relative to this point, so use with caution!</string>
<string name="preferences_clear_history_stats_error_toast">Unable to reset statistics - this device may not support this function\u2026</string>

<string name="preferences_custom_ref">The battery history will be based off of a custom reference point created now (or when the device gets unplugged). This can be used to determine what has used your battery since this specific point in time rather than since last unplugged or last charged. </string>
<string name="preferences_custom_ref_plugged">The device is currently charging - you may only create a custom reference when the device is unplugged.</string>
<string name="preferences_send_anon_stats_sum">Allow sending of anonymous usage statistics. No identifiable or private data is sent.</string>
<string name="preferences_show_ads_sum">Show ads in the main screen.</string>
<string name="preferences_override_lang_sum">Use a language other than your default system language.</string>

<string name="preferences_power_profiles_include_sensors_sum">"Some devices don't calculate sensor usage correctly. Uncheck this if your apps sensor usage seems inaccurate (accelerometer in particular). "</string>
<string name="preferences_power_profiles_include_sensors_dlg_msg">This will reset your power per percent calculation. Do you wish to continue?</string>
<string name="preferences_widget_color_preview_sum">Set the percent full value of the battery preview below.</string>
<string name="preferences_widget_color_screen_sum">Set the color gradient of the battery view, and control the widget settings</string>
<string name="process_suck_mon_nodata">No data available. There are no apps that have consumed the specified resource during the last device power cycle.</string>
<string name="main_android_batt_usage_failed">Unable to launch the built in battery usage screen...</string>
<string name="main_stat_ref_label">* Based on custom reference created %1s ago</string>
<string name="main_market_nomarket_msg">Function not available. There does not appear to be a market application installed on your device.</string>
<string name="main_share_subject">Average Battery Life - GSam Battery Monitor</string>
<string name="main_share_msg2">My %1$s %2$s battery averages %3$s (%4$s active usage) on a single charge. Check out GSam Battery Monitor: - http://bit.ly/uHT7Vy #badassbattery</string>
<string name="main_share_msg">My %1$s %2$s battery averages %3$s on a single charge. Check out GSam Battery Monitor monitor - http://bit.ly/uHT7Vy #badassbattery</string>
<string name="rate_me_msg">Do you like GSam Battery Monitor? Please take the time to give the app a good rating!\n\nDon\'t worry - you won\'t be asked again.</string>
<string name="appdetail_details_adjust_wifi">Turn off Wi-Fi when not in use using the Wi-Fi Settings button above.</string>
<string name="appdetail_details_adjust_screen">Lower screen brightness and screen timeout using the Display Settings button above.</string>
<string name="detail_menu_export_subject">GSam Labs - Battery Monitor - Export Data</string>
<!-- Change Log - actual change content isn't translated -->

<!-- NOTE: If they would like credit in the About screen, Translators can optionally put a name & optional HTML link. You can have > 1 name, just use <BR> The key should be in the form 'translator_lang'-->
<!-- Only Applicable to Paid/Pro Version (or marketing of said version) -->

<string name="appdetail_details_adjust_screen_market_bsd_msg">If you have trouble reading at night because your screen is too bright, check out GSam Screen Dimmer. It lets you reduce your brightness settings below what is normally allowed, making for a much more pleasant night-time read!\n\nDon\'t worry, you won\'t see this message again.</string>

<string name="preferences_send_anon_stats_buypro_msg">The free version of the Battery Monitor will not let you turn off ads if you choose to not allow anonymous usage statistics.\n\nThe Pro version does not include ads, and will let you turn off anonymous usage statistics.</string>
<string name="menu_seeotherapps">See Other Apps by GSam Labs</string>
<string name="menu_goprokindle">Upgrade To The Kindle Fire Edition</string>

<string name="nook_gopro_msg">Your trial of the battery monitor has expired. Please purchase the full edition. You can continue to use the battery monitor, however it will run in Free mode which removes a number of features and optimizations.</string>
<string name="main_market_pro_title">Thank You For Using GSam Battery Monitor - Free</string>

<string name="main_market_pro_msg">Did you know there is a Tablet optimized professional version of GSam Battery Monitor? Look for it in the market.\n\nDon\'t worry, you won\'t see this message again.</string>

<string name="main_market_pro_msg_kindle">Did you know there is a Kindle Fire optimized version of GSam Battery Monitor? Look for it in the Appstore.\n\nDon\'t worry, you won\'t see this message again.</string>

<string name="main_invalid_license_msg">Your license to this application appears to not be valid. The Battery Monitor will continue to operate in it\'s Free mode. If you feel this is a mistake, please check your purchase.</string>

<string name="about_invalidlicense">You do not have a valid license. GSam Battery Monitor will continue to run in Free mode. If you feel this is a mistake, please contact the developer with your Google Purchase ID</string>
